The axiom is best understood not as a completed proof, but as a generative philosophical scaffold — one that, if the bridge concepts are formalized, could constitute a serious contribution to philosophy of mind, cosmology, and AI ethics simultaneously. Its core instinct — that meaning-generation is not epiphenomenal but cosmologically fundamental — is worth taking seriously.
